Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: CBRE Limited (“CBRE”) has been retained as the exclusive sales representative for the sale of ±4.77-acre development land located on Principale-Est Avenue in Dieppe, New Brunswick. Conveniently woven into the desirable Dieppe community, this site represents an exceptional mixed-use development opportunity in a growing submarket. The property is just steps from a GoodLife, Aquatic Centre among others. Additionally, Coop IGA, Jean Coutu, and Dollarama is less than one block from the property, making grocery shopping a breeze for future tenants.The asset provides quick access to other parts of Greater Moncton due to convenient Champlain and Highway 15 access.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: CBRE Limited (“CBRE”) has been retained as the exclusive sales representative for the sale of ±0.87 ac development land located on Principale-Ouest Avenue in Dieppe, New Brunswick. Conveniently woven into the desirable Dieppe community, this site represents an exceptional multifamily development opportunity in a growing submarket. The property is just steps from a GoodLife, Aquatic Centre, among others. Additionally, Jean Coutu, Dollarama, and Coop IGA is less than one block from the property, making grocery shopping a breeze for future tenants.The asset provides quick access to other parts of Greater Moncton due to convenient Champlain and Highway 15 access. The site is within close proximity to multiple Transit Bus lines, providing easy access to public transportation.

Located at the entrance of Two Nations Crossing, the site has strong visibility and access ideal for a variety of uses ranging from quick service food to retail and general commercial uses. At roughly an acre in size, the property is suitable to local and national operators. It is anticipated that a new interchange at Two Nations Crossing will allow southbound traffic to enter the development. However, currently, the property benefits from an excellent position on St. Mary’s Street a commercial, professional services and automotive related hub on Fredericton’s north side. The site will be sold with a restrictive covenant against uses competitive with Canadian Tire, including the sale or installation of automotive parts and supplies, service or gas station, hardware store, sporting goods, hardware, building, plumbing or electrical supplies, paint and/or wallpaper, workwear apparel or a garden centre. Please contact CBRE for more details. See the Flyer for more information!
